<ns562:section xmlns:ns562="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.documenting.rup.4Plus1View.4Plus1View">

  <ns563:title xmlns:ns563="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">4+1 View of Software Architecture</ns563:title>
  <ns564:para xmlns:ns564="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    RUP suggests that a reference architecture should be defined along different levels of abstraction, 
    or "views," thereby providing more flexibility in how it can be used. Ideally, these views map to the 
    4+1 Views of software architecture outlined in the RUP (see 
    <ns565:xref xmlns:ns565="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.concepts.architecture.referenceArchitectures.introduction.rup4Plus1View_fig"/>)
    and embodied in the RUP's Software Architecture Document.        
  </ns564:para>
  <ns566:figure xmlns:ns566="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.referenceArchitectures.introduction.rup4Plus1View_fig">
    <ns567:title xmlns:ns567="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"/>
    <mediaobject xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><imageobject><imagedata fileref="rup4Plus1View.jpg"/></imageobject></mediaobject>
  </ns566:figure>
  
  <ns568:section xmlns:ns568="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns569:title xmlns:ns569="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The logical view</ns569:title>
    <ns570:para xmlns:ns570="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The logical view focuses on how the functional requirements of the system are to be realized.
       This view is usually represented by object model of the design. 
    </ns570:para>  
  </ns568:section>
  
  <ns571:section xmlns:ns571="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns572:title xmlns:ns572="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The process view</ns572:title>
    <ns573:para xmlns:ns573="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The process view focuses on how the non-functional requirements like
       <ns574:itemizedlist xmlns:ns574="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns575:listitem xmlns:ns575="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns576:para xmlns:ns576="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">performance,</ns576:para></ns575:listitem>
         <ns577:listitem xmlns:ns577="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns578:para xmlns:ns578="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">reliability,</ns578:para></ns577:listitem>
         <ns579:listitem xmlns:ns579="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns580:para xmlns:ns580="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">modifiability,</ns580:para></ns579:listitem>
         <ns581:listitem xmlns:ns581="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns582:para xmlns:ns582="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">security,</ns582:para></ns581:listitem>
         <ns583:listitem xmlns:ns583="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns584:para xmlns:ns584="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">manageability, and so on</ns584:para></ns583:listitem>
       </ns574:itemizedlist>
       are realized. In other words, it looks at the <ns585:emphasis xmlns:ns585="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">realization of the required quality
       attributes</ns585:emphasis> for the system.
    </ns573:para>
    <ns586:para xmlns:ns586="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      For example, in order to address performance it will look at concurrencies, synchronization
      points, number of layers, protocol marshalling/demarshalling and so forth.
    </ns586:para>
  </ns571:section>
  
  <ns587:section xmlns:ns587="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns588:title xmlns:ns588="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The implementation view</ns588:title>
    <ns589:para xmlns:ns589="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The implementation view <ns590:emphasis xmlns:ns590="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> focuses on the actual architecture as it is realized by combining 
      architectural patterns</ns590:emphasis>.
      This view looks at the actual software module organization and may also point out the software
      development environment. 
    </ns589:para>
  </ns587:section>
  

  <ns591:section xmlns:ns591="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns592:title xmlns:ns592="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The deployment view</ns592:title>
    <ns593:para xmlns:ns593="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The physical view describes the mapping(s) of the software onto the hardware and reflects its 
      distributed aspect. This view should show <ns594:emphasis xmlns:ns594="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">how hardware architecture is to be used 
      to realize some of the quality attributes</ns594:emphasis> required by th system.
    </ns593:para>
  </ns591:section>
    
</ns562:section>